{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01VeBATiWQ8XEze6dhin83FD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is deployed and fully operational.\n\n## Summary\n\nA 3-node CockroachDB cluster is running in the `cockroachdb` namespace, built entirely from native Kubernetes resources (no operator, no CRDs).\n\n**Resources created:**\n| Resource | Name | Details |\n|---|---|---|\n| Headless Service | `crdb-cluster` | `clusterIP: None`, exposes grpc 26257 + http 8080, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` for peer discovery |\n| Public Service | `crdb-cluster-public` | ClusterIP, grpc 26257 + http 8080 |\n| StatefulSet | `crdb-cluster` | 3 replicas, image `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `crdb-cluster` | `maxUnavailable: 1` — preserves quorum during voluntary disruptions |\n| PVCs | `datadir-crdb-cluster-{0,1,2}` | 10Gi each, all Bound |\n\n**Key configuration:**\n- Each pod advertises by its stable DNS name (`$(hostname).crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`) and `--join` lists all 3 nodes.\n- `--insecure` (no TLS) as required.\n- Uses the existing `crdb-cluster-sa` ServiceAccount / RBAC; no new RBAC created.\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all 3 pods start together (the default `OrderedReady` deadlocks: pods aren't Ready until the cluster is initialized, but init needs all pods up).\n- Ran `cockroach init --insecure` once to bootstrap the cluster.\n\n**Verification:**\n- StatefulSet `3/3` ready; all pods `1/1 Running`.\n- `cockroach node status` shows all 3 nodes `is_available=true`, `is_live=true`.\n- PDB reports `ALLOWED DISRUPTIONS: 1`, guaranteeing ≥2 of 3 nodes stay available during voluntary disruptions (quorum preserved).\n\nThe manifest is saved at `stages/stage_01/crdb.yaml`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":479,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1790,"cache_read_input_tokens":39751,"cache_creation":{"ep